deck: Tombstone orders Eddie to defeat Spider-Man and Peter feels guilty for neglecting his family and friends.
name: Nature vs. Nurture

deck: Spidey faces a new challenge, Mysterio.
name: Blueprints

description: Bruce Wayne is framed for foul play against Lucius Fox regarding conspiracy and attempted murder. The mystery deepens with Bruce Wayne, as Batman, learns of a prior actor- Matt Hagen- and his ties to an experimental facial reconstruction cream by Roland Daggett leaves the selfish actor deformed as the malleable villain Clayface (Hagen).
name: Feat of Clay, Part One

description: Bruce Wayne is released from prison on bail. Hagen, as it turns out, survived the murder attempt on him, but at a high cost: the formula entered his body and soaked every single one of his cells, turning him into a shape-shifting mutant. With his newfound powers, Hagen, now calling himself Clayface, decides to take his revenge on Daggett and his men.
name: Feat of Clay, Part Two

description: Working everyman, Charlie Collins, gets caught in a road-side fight with the Joker which leaves him to do Joker a favor for his life . During James Gordon's Inaugural police banquet of service, Charlie has one shot to stop Joker from being the "death of the party", but he needs and gets Batman to help him.
name: Joker's Favor

description: Lloyd "Eddie" Ventrix is on the verge of losing his daughter, Kimberly, to his ex-wife, Helen, due to his past as a con artist. Determined not to lose Kimberly, Ventrix dons a suit, stolen from where he used to work while on parole, which grants the user invisibility but also becomes highly toxic, and poses as Kimberly's imaginary friend, Mojo, while stealing jewellery for her.
name: See No Evil

description: Note: This episode marks Tuffy's on screen debut.
name: The Milky Waif

description: Batman investigates a cult, called the Brotherhood, founded by the "mystic" Nostromos after hearing about a number of stories from his colleagues about his ability to predict the future. Batman finds out that Nostromos is actually a con artist who was rigging near-fatal accidents to gain the confidence of Gotham's upper class citizens.
name: Prophecy of Doom

description: The leader of the Red Claw group attacks a military train and steals a viral plague, which she intends to release in Gotham if she isn't paid a ransom.
name: The Cat and the Claw, Part Two

description: Obsessive-compulsive businessman, Temple Fugate, sets to uphold a 7 year vendetta toward Mayor Hamilton Hill for making him late to a multi-million dollar court case that left him late and broke from Hamilton's advice. Set to ruin the mayor on his since bankruptcy, Clock King has since taken precisions to ruin Hamilton Hill's re-election and life- unless Batman can save the mayor in time.
name: The Clock King

description: With the help of arsonists, Roland Daggett plans to destroy Crime Alley and use the land to expand his business empire. But that plan would mean killing the residents or forcing them to abandon their homes. Now, Batman must foil Daggett's plan and try to prove that he is a criminal.
name: Appointment in Crime Alley

description: Miserable Wayne Industries scientist Jervis Tetch is unable to pursue the girl he loves, Alice the secretary. When she splits up from her boyfriend, he makes an advance and develops a fast friendship with her, until her boyfriend reconciles with her and proposes to her. Enraged, Tetch decides to take matters into his own hands, and dons the mantle of the Mad Hatter, using his mind-control devices to force those who have wronged him all his life to become his mindless slaves.
name: Mad as a Hatter

description: Batman is incarcerated in Arkham Asylum after being exposed to the Scarecrow's fear-inducing gas. Batman knows that the Scarecrow has escaped for the second time and is planning to poison Gotham's water supply with the same fear-inducing gas.
name: Dreams in Darkness

description: Tom emerges from a beach hut with a long red bathing suit on but gets his suit caught in the door which causes him to snap back when he tries to dive in the sea. He dives in again but the water recedes so he swims in debris, and exits to take a stroll along the beach. During his stroll, he notices a beautiful white cat, and he ends up falling in a garbage bin, and is ejected out onto the female's lap. In an attempt to impress her, he drinks her soda and eats her hot dog. Then a tomato and banana peal land on his head, and finds Jerry inside the basket eating all the food. Tom fails to swat him with a flyswatter and Jerry throws eggs into his eyes and bites on a piece of celery through the cat's hand, making him scream. Tom chases Jerry, who hides in a pile of rocks, and Tom pulls out a crab accidentally, who removes his whiskers and snaps on his tail, making him scream again. Tom finds Jerry and chases him again, but Jerry manages to trap Tom in a beach umbrella and Tom lies on the floor with his upper body covered by the umbrella cloth. To triple Tom's pain, Jerry has the crab run up Tom's trouser leg and pinch his butt, causing the cat to scream again and jump, which causes the peak of the umbrella to dig in the sand, leaving them upside down. To embarrass Tom greatly, the crab leaves Tom's butt showing off by creating a square flap to escape, which means anyone on the beach can see Tom's butt.
name: Salt Water Tabby
Tom and Jerry in the Hollywood Bowl

description: , Bruce Wayne retires due to failing health when his rescue of a kidnapped woman nearly goes wrong and he must resort to almost using a gun—the ultimate sin in his eyes. Twenty years later, Terry McGinnis discovers Batman's identity after the aging Bruce Wayne helps him fight off a gang of jokerz (street punks enamored of the original clown prince of crime). After Terry's father is murdered, Terry seeks Bruce's help to avenge him.
name: Rebirth, Part 1

description: Terry steals the Batsuit to pursue his father's killer, a professional bodyguard named Mr. Fixx whose employer Derek Powers the current CEO of Wayne-Powers, is secretly using the company's resources to develop a biological weapon. Bruce Wayne, discovering the theft, deactivates the suit, but when seeing the now-helpless Terry being punched out reactivates it so he can continue pursuing Fixx, and in the end Wayne appears at Terry's house to hire him as a "special assistant."
name: Rebirth, Part 2

description: Terry, having just started to work for Bruce Wayne, faces off against Inque , a notorious mercenary who is sabotaging FoxTeca, a company formed by Lucius Fox's son.
name: Black Out

description: Willie Watt, a high school nerd who has been picked on one too many times, steals a construction robot from his father to scare his chief tormentor, Nelson Nash. But when Batman tries to stop the robot, it becomes bonded to Willie mentally, giving him more power than he ever dreamed of.
name: Golem
